from collections import Counter
t = int(input())
for i in range(t):
    n = int(input())
    l = list(map(int, input().split()))
    ob = Counter(l)
    k = [x for x in ob.values()]
    p = max(k)
    c = 0
    for y in range(len(k)):
        if k[y] == p:
            c += 1
    if c == 1:
        key_list = list(ob.keys())
        pos = k.index(p)
        print(key_list[pos])
    else:
        print('CONFUSED')

t = int(input())
while t > 0:
    n = int(input())
    list1 = list(map(int, input().split()))
    list3 = []
    m = 0
    val = 0
    f = 0
    fl = 0
    for i in list1:
        if i not in list3:
            list3.append(i)
            c = list1.count(i)
            if f == 0:
                m = c
                f = 1
                val = i
            elif c > m:
                m = c
                val = i
                fl = 0
            elif c == m:
                fl = 1
    if fl == 1:
        print('CONFUSED')

        print(val)
